Pupils at a primary school in Kabuchayi, in the county of Bungoma have been forced to endure lessons under roofless classrooms after the classrooms were blown away by heavy winds. Chenjeni primary school headteacher, Samuel Ndamwe, says the incident has caused too much destruction thus putting a huge strain on the school besides disrupting learning for hundreds of pupils. Area leaders have however appealed to well?wishers to assist in roofing the classrooms.